A07. Find Duplicates in a Slice
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM:
  Given a slice of integers, return all elements that appear more than once.

APPROACH:
  Single pass with a frequency map.

CODE:
  package main

  import "fmt"

  func findDuplicates(nums []int) []int {
      freq := make(map[int]int)
      for _, n := range nums {
          freq[n]++
      }

      var result []int
      for val, count := range freq {
          if count > 1 {
              result = append(result, val)
          }
      }
      return result
  }

  func main() {
      fmt.Println(findDuplicates([]int{1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3, 5}))
      // [2 3] (order may vary — map iteration is random in Go)
  }

COMPLEXITY:
  Time:  O(n)
  Space: O(n)

NOTE:
  Output order is non-deterministic — sort if order matters.
  Mention this to the interviewer.

