D03. Rate Limiter Using Ticker
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM:
  Process requests but limit to 3 per second using a ticker.

CODE:
  package main

  import (
      "fmt"
      "time"
  )

  func main() {
      requests := make(chan int, 10)
      for i := 1; i <= 8; i++ {
          requests <- i
      }
      close(requests)

      // Allow 1 request every 333ms = ~3 per second
      limiter := time.NewTicker(333 * time.Millisecond)
      defer limiter.Stop()

      for req := range requests {
          <-limiter.C // wait for tick
          fmt.Printf("request %d processed at %v\n",
              req, time.Now().Format("15:04:05.000"))
      }
  }

PATTERN: Rate Limiting with time.Ticker

NOTE:
  For bursty rate limiting (allow burst then throttle), use a buffered
  channel filled by a ticker goroutine.

